<br>
Theoretically you can max out your tradeskill without killing a monster.  This is true for the beginning to early mid levels.  But the exp you get for an item is based on the difference between the skills minimum required skill to make, and your current skill.  So just like in EQ, you've got trivial items that don't give you much exp.  In the beginning you can just walk out to mines and get ore from the earth, but higher quality ore is generally placed in areas with appropriate leveled monsters guarding it.  So the only way to get it is to buy the raw ore from other players - if you chose not to advance your Adventure school.<br>
<br>
-Takkon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhaxalygen>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/03 11:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2010.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Dungeons and Dragons</span><hr size=1> What's the latest version/game of D and D? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syllestraefv>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3804<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/03 6:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2010.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dungeons and Dragons</span><hr size=1> There's Neverwinter Nights, and Temple of Elemental Evil.<br>
